The Prague stock market was down by the end of the trade
The Prague Stock Exchange corrected its losses after the rapid fall in the morning.
Transactions in shares in the Czech Energy Enterprise (ČEZ) reached nearly half of the usual daily trade.
The Prague Stock Exchange continued its Monday fall immediately from the start of Tuesday's trade when it fell almost six percent.
This time, the fall in Wall Street shares is behind the decline.
This is how the market reacts to the outcome of the U.S. House of Representatives vote, which refused to support the stabilisation plan for the financial sector there.
Shares falling in Asia
Asian stock markets experienced a dramatic drop in shares on Tuesday, although some of the losses were eventually cancelled during the day.
The Hong Kong Hang Seng stock market index described almost four percent during trading, but later deleted some of the losses and reduced the decline to about 2.5 percent.
On the Hong Kong Stock Exchange, Hang Seng China Enterprises Index, monitoring Chinese shares, dropped 3.8 percent, and markets in Shanghai were closed.
Stocks in the Sydney Stock Exchange lost more than five percent, but eventually losses fell to 4.3 percent.
The Taiwan stock market dropped 3.6 percent according to the index there.
"The timing of the U.S. rescue operation is uncertain and affects the world's financial markets," noted Joseph Yam, head of the Hong Kong Finance Council.
Hong Kong, although part of China, determines its financial policy independently, i.e. independently of the Chinese central bank.
In Hong Kong, interest rates are at the same level as in the United States.
According to Australian Prime Minister Kevin Rudd, U.S. legislators should immediately resume negotiations and accept the financial system's proposal for support.
Otherwise, there is a threat that other countries will feel the consequences of this.
The Bloodbath of American Stocks
The U.S. House of Representatives rejected the draft financial system support on Monday, to which $700 billion (almost 12 trillion crowns) should have been spent.
The legislators thus ignored President George Bush's call to support the plan.
Bush says the draft would solve the main causes of the financial crisis and help stabilize the entire economy.
On Monday, US shares experienced a bloodbath and leading stock indices recorded the largest fall in 20 years.
The Dow Jones fell almost seven percent, a similar rate of fall was most recently experienced in 1987.
The index fell before the vote, but as it turned out that the proposal was not adopted in the House of Representatives, the index began to fall free.
Congress withdrew: U.S. government can pump $700 billion into banks
Supreme leaders of the U.S. Congress and the government of President George W. Bush agreed on a broader form of agreement and financial assistance for the U.S. financial system.
This will be voted on early next week.
U.S. legislators have made a breakthrough in negotiations for the approval of the rescue plan in the form of financial assistance to the U.S. financial system in the amount of $700 billion (approximately 12 trillion krona).
But there's no victory yet.
Congress must complete some details of the agreement before they can make public the final form of the law and their vote.
The draft funding for the financial system will be discussed in the House of Representatives on Monday.
This was informed Sunday by Reuters news agency Barney Frank, chairman of the Committee on Financial Organizations.
According to Senate sources, they are likely to vote on the draft as soon as possible on Wednesday.
According to economists, there should be an announcement that the rescue plan will be approved, which is the first important psychological factor in reviving the financial markets.
However, due to the complexity of the mechanisms, a "equilibrium" will then take place.
Paulson: The plan must be effective
"We've taken a big step.
We have resolved our differing views on what the form of a package to stabilise the market should be," said Bloomberg agency Democrat Nancy Pelosi.
According to him, the final vote could take place on Sunday.
Legislative representatives met Henry Paulson, the U.S. Finance Minister, on Saturday night to give a final form to the government fund.
This should buy from financial companies the unsellable mortgage activities that lead financial firms to heavy losses and jeopardise the stability of the whole system.
"We are close to the final agreement on a draft that will work and which should also be effective on the market.
The reform plan still needs to be continued, but I think we're there," said Paulson.
Signal to Asian Trading
The global financial crisis has a significant impact on the stock markets, which are falling violently.
According to Nevada Democratic Senator Harry Reid, the legislators therefore seek to reach a final settlement in Congress on Sunday.
This is to reassure investors before trading in the Asian financial markets, where the decision of Congress could be the first to influence trading on Monday due to the time zone.
However, it is not yet clear when the two chambers of the U.S. Congress are voting on the law, nor is it whether the trial can be stalled at the last minute due to a problem.
Legislators hope that the law will be approved in the next few days.
However, the law is still undergoing a number of changes.
The total amount intended to assist the system shall be divided into two parts.
As requested by President George Bush, the first $350 billion should be available as soon as possible.
However, Congress may block the issuance of the remaining amount, which was set at an additional $100 billion and later $350 billion, if it feels that the program does not fulfil its function.
Bush assessed progress in the negotiations
Although the President may veto this resolution, Congress may override its veto.
Despite these changes, however, the basic idea of the program remained, which was to acquire financial assets for the acquisition of bad mortgage securities that lost their value, as hundreds of thousands of Americans were unable to repay their mortgages.
"We've worked it all out.
The law should be able for the House of Representatives to vote on Sunday and for the Senate on Monday," said Republican Senator Judd Gregg.
US President Bush is also satisfied with the progress made in the negotiations.
Tony Fratto, Bush's spokesperson, stated that the president was satisfied with the progress made on Saturday and appreciates the "bipartisan efforts made to stabilise our financial markets and defend our economy".
Limitation of Bushy severance payments
The chairman of the Senate Banking Committee, Christopher Dodd, who led the negotiations, said that the legislators had agreed on the responsibility for the financial program, the protection of taxpayers from losses, the closure of benefits, and the timing of the funding draft.
The new law also limits the so-called busy severance payments of the directors involved in the programme and establishes a board of supervisors of the fund.
The fund should be run by the Treasury Department.
"We have worked very hard on this and we have made great progress towards an agreement that will work and which will be useful to all Americans," said Paulson.
The plan also expects help to homeowners who have problems with repayment.
The government should negotiate new repayment instalments at the mortgages it buys, with the aim of reducing the monthly instalments of debtors and allowing them to keep their houses.
Marek: Spiritual Aid
According to David Marek, the chief economist at Patria Finance, the proposed draft is a good idea, but its implementation will be very difficult.
"All because it is not possible to know by what mechanism and at what price the problematic assets will be acquired.
This will determine how the financial sector and the government distribute losses among themselves," said Marek to iHNed.cz website this week.
According to Marek, it is not so important that the plan is approved now or early next week.
"It is much more important for Congress to decide already this week to support the plan and to give their blessing as soon as possible.
The spiritual significance of agreeing that the plan will be approved is the most important thing at this moment," stressed Marek.
