Not at the window of the bank teller, where money can be picked up or paid in, but at the customer service desk, where older customers order a checkbook, tourists ask for directions to Macy's store, and where new customers open a bank account.
Many before me - I later learned from Starr, the "ordered" banker - lined up with the same intention as me.
However, unlike me, they have already taken their money from smaller banks in their homes, such as New Jersey, Pennsylvania, and Staten Island.
Money was taken out from savings banks (which are such as housing cooperatives), credit unions, and small-town savings banks that operate in only one state and are said to treat their clients as family members.
