Muslim tombs were desecrated while Austria tilted to the right
Heinz-Christian Strache, of the right-wing Austrian Freedom Party, and Filip Dewinter, of the Belgian right-wing party Vlaams Belang, participated in a demonstration in Antwerp, Thursday, January 17, 2008 in which the organization "Cityers Against the Expansion of Islam" was introduced.
They marched with emulating signs of traffic signs depicting mosques drawn through a red line.
Police say far-right extremists are responsible for desecrating Muslim cemeteries in Austria, which occurred on the same weekend that far-right parties significantly advanced in national parliamentary elections.
More than 90 graves were severely damaged in the Traunian cemetery near Linz, sometime between Friday night and this morning.
The perpetrators drew Jewish symbols, such as David's star, on some graves, but investigators said this was only trying to hide their extreme motives, which stem from hatred against Muslim immigrants.
