A written version of the $700 billion Economic Rescue Package Act, applicable in several instalments to buy bad loans from banks, has been completed.
In the first round, half the amount is spent.
During further discussions on East Coast time until after midnight on Saturday, Congressional leaders reached a conclusion in the days-long debate around a total bailout package of $700 billion, Reuters reported.
